PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
A-ENGROSSED HOUSE BILL 4061
1 On page 1 of the printed A-engrossed bill, delete lines 4 through 6 and
2 insert:
3 “SECTION 1. Notwithstanding any other law limiting expenditures,
4 the limitation on expenditures established by section 11 (1), chapter
5 616, Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium ending June 30, 2027, as the
6 maximum limit for payment of expenses from lottery moneys allocated
7 from the Administrative Services Economic Development Fund to the
8 Oregon Business Development Department, for operations, is in-
9 creased by $235,846, for implementation of section 2 of this 2026 Act.
10 “SECTION 1a. Notwithstanding any other law limiting expendi-
11 tures, the limitation on expenditures established by section 11 (2),
12 chapter 616, Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium ending June 30, 2027,
13 as the maximum limit for payment of expenses from lottery moneys
14 allocated from the Administrative Services Economic Development
15 Fund to the Oregon Business Development Department, for business,
16 innovation and trade, is increased by $950,000, for micro-enterprise
17 tariff adjustment grants under section 2 of this 2026 Act.”.
18 On page 2, delete lines 25 through 45 and delete pages 3 and 4 and insert:
19 “SECTION 5. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate
20 preservation of the public peace, health and safety, an emergency is
21 declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect on its passage.”.

